The '''Basic Education College''' is a degree-awarding [[Tertiary education|tertiary]] institute in [[Kuwait]]. It is one of the four colleges operated by the Government's [[The Public Authority for Applied Education and Training]] ([[PAAET]]) and is part of the nation's applied education sector.<ref>[http://www.kuwait-info.com/a_education/education_applied.asp "The Public Authority for Applied Education and Training (PAAET)"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080917092922/http://www.kuwait-info.com/a_education/education_applied.asp |date=September 17, 2008 }}, Ministry of Information, Kuwait</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20041015183628/http://www.aiwfonline.co.uk/downloads/dr%20fayzah.pdf "Higher Education in Kuwait"], Arab International Women's Conference, 22 October 2003</ref>

The College is affiliated with the [[E-TQM College]], the world's first online school for the field of [[Total Quality Management]] (TQM).<ref>[http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-22710125_ITM "e-TQM, Kuwait college sign education deal"], [[Gulf News]], 16 March 2003</ref>

The college provides teachers to the Ministry of Education as part of their drive to improve standards.<ref>[http://www.kuwaittimes.net/read_news.php?newsid=MTEyNDk1NzQ2MQ== "Ministry assures better education"]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110726003646/http://www.kuwaittimes.net/read_news.php?newsid=MTEyNDk1NzQ2MQ%3D%3D |date=July 26, 2011  }}, [[Kuwait Times]], September 17, 2008</ref> 

