{{Other people|David Griffiths}} {{Infobox scientist | name = David J. Griffiths | image = David Griffiths giving autograph.jpg | caption = David Griffiths giving autograph to students at [[Indian Institute of Technology Kanpur|IIT Kanpur]] | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1942|12|05}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | residence = | nationality = | ethnicity = | field = [[Physics]] | work_institution = [[Reed College]] | alma_mater = [[Harvard University]] | doctoral_advisor = [[Sidney Coleman]] | doctoral_students = | known_for = | awards = | signature = Griffiths-signature-vectorized.svg | signature_alt = | footnotes = |}} '''David Jeffrey Griffiths''' (born 1942) is a [[United States|U.S.]] [[physics|physicist]] and educator. He worked at [[Reed College]] from 1978 through 2009, becoming the [[Howard Vollum]] Professor of Science before his retirement. He is not to be confused with the late physicist David J. Griffiths of [[Oregon State University]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Landau, Rubin H.|title=In Memoriam: David John Griffiths|newspaper=Oregon State U. Physics Newsletter|volume=1|issue=1|date=Jan 2007|page=2|url=http://physics.oregonstate.edu/files/physics/PhysicNews12-06.pdf}}</ref>
==Biography== Griffiths is a graduate of [[The Putney School]] and was trained at [[Harvard University]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]], 1964; [[Master's degree|M.A.]], 1966; [[Doctor of Philosophy|Ph.D.]], 1970). His doctoral work ("[[Covariance|Covariant]] Approach to Massless Field Theory in the Radiation Gauge") on theoretical [[particle physics]] was supervised by [[Sidney Coleman]]. He is principally known as the author of three highly regarded textbooks for [[undergraduate]] physics students: ''Introduction to Elementary Particles'' (published in 1987, second edition published 2008), ''Introduction to Quantum Mechanics'' (published in 1995, third edition published 2018), and ''Introduction to Electrodynamics'' (published in 1981, fourth edition published in 2012). He was also the recipient of the 1997 [[Robert A. Millikan award]] reserved for "those who have made outstanding scholarly contributions to physics education".<ref name=Griffiths1997>{{cite journal |last=Griffiths |first=David |authorlink=David Griffiths (physicist) |date=December 1997 |title=Millikan Lecture 1997: Is there a text in this class? |journal=American Journal of Physics |volume=65 |issue=12 |pages=1141–1143 |url=http://scitation.aip.org/vsearch/servlet/VerityServlet?KEY=AJPIAS&CURRENT=NO&ONLINE=YES&smode=strresults&sort=rel&maxdisp=25&threshold=0&pjournals=AJPIAS&pyears=2001%2C2000%2C1999&possible1=1141&possible1zone=fpage&fromvolume=65&SMODE=strsearch&OUTLOG=NO&viewabs=AJPIAS&key=DISPLAY&docID=1&page=1&chapter=0 |accessdate=2007-05-22 |doi=10.1119/1.18777 |bibcode=1997AmJPh..65.1141G}}</ref><ref>[http://www.aapt.org/Programs/awards/millikan.cfm List of Robert A. Millikan Award Winners at the American Association of Physics Teachers website]</ref> In 2009 he was named a Fellow of the [[American Physical Society]].<ref>{{cite web|title=New APS Fellows Nominated from the Forum of Education|website=APS Physics, Forum on Education|date=Spring 2010|url=http://www.aps.org/units/fed/newsletters/spring2010/fellows.cfm}}</ref>
==Books== *{{cite book |last=Griffiths |first=David |authorlink=David Griffiths (physicist) | title=Introduction to Elementary Particles (2nd ed.) | publisher=[[Wiley-VCH]] | year=2008 | url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Introduction_to_Elementary_Particles.html?id=Wb9DYrjcoKAC | isbn=3-527-40601-8}} *{{cite book |last=Griffiths |first=David |authorlink=David Griffiths (physicist) | title=Introduction to Electrodynamics (4th ed.) | publisher=[[Addison-Wesley]] | year=2012 | isbn=0-321-85656-2}} *{{cite book|title=[[Introduction to Quantum Mechanics (Griffiths)|Introduction to Quantum Mechanics]] (2nd ed.)|last=Griffiths|first=David|publisher=[[Prentice Hall]]|year=2004|isbn=0-13-111892-7|location=|pages=|authorlink=David Griffiths (physicist)}} *{{cite book |last=Griffiths |first=David |authorlink=David Griffiths (physicist) | title=Revolutions in Twentieth-Century Physics | publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]] | year=2012 | url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Revolutions_in_Twentieth_Century_Physics.html?id=Tv8cz-kN2z0C | isbn=978-1-107-60217-5}}<ref>{{cite journal|author=Abernathy, William|title=Review of ''Revolutions in Twentieth-Century Physics'' by David Griffiths|journal=Reed Magazine|date=Sep 2013|volume=92|issue=3|url=http://www.reed.edu/reed_magazine/september2013/articles/reediana/griffiths.html}}</ref>
