'''Greentop Community Circus Centre''' is the only Circus School in Yorkshire, northern England, and was established in 1995 on the TV programme ''[[Challenge Anneka]]'',<ref>{{cite web|date=1 June 2010 |url=http://www.sheffieldtelegraph.co.uk/lifestyle/new_challenge_for_community_circus_1_802909 |title=New challenge for community circus - Lifestyle |publisher=Sheffield Telegraph |accessdate=2012-02-20}}</ref> and is one of three UK circus schools providing accredited level training courses in circus skills.<ref name=hub>{{cite web|title=Greentop Community Circus Centre|url=http://www.financehub.org.uk/greentopcommunitycircuscentre.aspa|publisher=The Finance Hub|accessdate=18 June 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111001141517/http://www.financehub.org.uk/greentopcommunitycircuscentre.aspa|archivedate=1 October 2011}}</ref>
The school was founded and run by volunteers before investment from the Arts Council England,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.artscouncil.org.uk/funding/browse-regularly-funded-organisations/npo/greentop-community-circus-centre/ |title=Greentop Community Circus Centre |publisher=Arts Council |date= |accessdate=2013-02-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130208230608/http://www.artscouncil.org.uk/funding/browse-regularly-funded-organisations/npo/greentop-community-circus-centre/ |archivedate=2013-02-08 |df= }}</ref> provided funds for paid staff.<ref>{{cite web | title = Caroline bows out after ensuring the show goes on | work = Sheffield Telegraph | publisher = | date = 31 March 2009 | url = http://www.sheffieldtelegraph.co.uk/lifestyle/caroline_bows_out_after_ensuring_the_show_goes_on_1_452915?action=logout | accessdate = 7 March 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/news/around-yorkshire/local-stories/high_flier_learns_the_ropes_1_2333735 |title=High flier learns the ropes - Local stories |publisher=Yorkshire Post |date=2009-02-04 |accessdate=2012-02-20}}</ref> Public funding is complemented by earned income through social enterprises.<ref name=hub/>
The school is a founder member of the UK Circus Training Action Group alongside three other UK circus schools: [[The Circus Space]], [[Circomedia]], and Skylight. It is based in the former church of [[St Thomas, Brightside]].<ref>"[http://www.thestar.co.uk/news/big-top-tips-for-budding-performers-1-5590622 Big top tips for budding performers]", ''[[The Star (Sheffield)|The Star]]'', 18 April 2013</ref>
