'''Robert Michael Morris''' (May 6, 1940 – May 30, 2017) was an American actor. He was known for his co-starring role as Mickey Deane in the [[reality television]] spoof ''[[The Comeback (TV series)|The Comeback]]''<ref name="etvs">{{cite book|last1=Terrace|first1=Vincent|title=Encyclopedia of Television Shows, 1925 through 2010|date=2011|publisher=McFarland & Company, Inc., Publishers|location=Jefferson, N.C.|isbn=978-0-7864-6477-7|pages=201–202|edition=2nd}}</ref> and as Mr. Lunt in the short-lived series ''[[Running Wilde]]''. He also wrote over 100 plays.
==Biography== Born in [[Kentucky]], Morris obtained a [[Bachelor of Arts]] in English and art from the [[University of Dayton]], as well as a [[Master of Fine Arts]] in playwriting from the [[Catholic University of America]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/robert-michael-morris-dead-comeback-actor-was-77-1008834 |title=Robert Michael Morris, ''The Comeback'' Actor, Dies at 77 |last=Huff |first=Lauren |date=May 30, 2017 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=May 30, 2017}}</ref> He taught both high school and college theater before becoming a professional actor relatively late in life and relocating to [[New York City]]. "I moved to New York so I could find out what it was like to be a professional actor because my students were all asking questions and all I had was academic knowledge. I didn't have any real professional knowledge."<ref>[http://www.newnownext.com/robert-michael-morris-is-running-wilde-again/09/2010/2/ Robert Michael Morris is “Running Wilde” Again]</ref> [[Michael Patrick King]], one of Morris's students, and [[Lisa Kudrow]] wrote his role in ''The Comeback'' with him in mind; King asked him to audition.<ref name ="RMM">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2017/05/robert-michael-morris-dies-the-comeback-actor-died-1202104330/ |title=Robert Michael Morris Dies: ''The Comeback'' Actor Was 77 |last=Petski |first=Denise |date=May 30, 2017 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=May 30, 2017}}</ref>
Morris also had notable guest appearances in such series as ''[[Will & Grace]]'', ''[[How I Met Your Mother]]'', ''[[Better Things (TV series)|Better Things]]'' and ''[[2 Broke Girls]]''.
Morris died on May 30, 2017, at age 77.<ref name ="RMM" />
